“WHAT YOU REFUSE TO RELEASE”

📍 QUEST LOCATION
The Gilded Expanse
A vast, ruined metropolis of vaults, temples, archives, armories, and sealed memories. Gold, relics, knowledge, titles, names, and promises are embedded into the walls themselves.
Greed here is possession, not currency.

🎯 PRIMARY OBJECTIVE
Reach the Hall of Appraisal and descend to the Arena of Greed without being consumed by attachment.

🧭 QUEST FLOW & OBJECTIVES
OBJECTIVE 1: ENTER THE GILDED EXPANSE
Task: Step into the Circle of Greed.
The moment the player enters, the UI introduces a hidden system: Burden (not explained).
The environment reacts to what the player already carries:
Equipped gear whispers.
Rings pulse faintly.
NPC echoes comment on “what you brought with you.”
Gameplay:
Exploration + light combat.

OBJECTIVE 2: THE OFFERINGS
Task: Navigate the Expanse while encountering Temptation Nodes.
These appear as:
Relics
Sealed vaults
Forgotten contracts
Memories turned into items
Each offering:
Gives a powerful benefit
Adds Burden
The player is never told how much Burden they have.

OBJECTIVE 3: MANAGE THE WEIGHT
Task: Survive traversal as Burden increases.
As Burden rises:
Dodge windows shorten
Movement becomes heavier
Enemy aggression increases
Certain paths collapse or appear based on what you hold
New Mechanic:
The player can drop or abandon items at altars of release.
Dropping:
Weakens the player temporarily
Restores movement and clarity
Alters dialogue and environment reactions

OBJECTIVE 4: POSSESSION COMBAT
Task: Survive ambushes by Hoardbound Enemies.
Enemy behavior:
Target relics instead of HP
Steal buffs mid-fight
Imitate abilities granted by your items
Player Choice:
Chase and reclaim stolen power
Or let it go and move on
Letting go is mechanically safer but emotionally costly.

OBJECTIVE 5: THE MIRROR VAULTS
Task: Cross three mirrored chambers.
Each chamber reflects:
What you collected
What you refused to drop
What you lost
In each vault:
The player fights a distorted echo of themselves
The echo uses abilities based on your current Burden
Victory opens the path forward — but increases pressure.

OBJECTIVE 6: THE HALL OF APPRAISAL
Task: Face judgment before the descent.
The Hall evaluates:
Total Burden
Items carried
Items abandoned
Times you reclaimed stolen power
NPC Judges speak in neutral, cold tones:
“You cling.”
“You calculate.”
“You could have released.”
The arena layout shifts based on your behavior.

OBJECTIVE 7: THE FINAL DECISION
Task: Choose how to open the descent.
Two paths:
🔒 SEAL THE VAULT
Requires abandoning most relics
Descent opens cleanly
Boss fight favors control and restraint
🔨 FORCE IT OPEN
Keep everything
Arena is hostile and unstable
Boss mocks ownership and entitlement
No choice is labeled “good” or “bad.”

OBJECTIVE 8: DESCEND
Task: Enter the Arena of Greed.
Your Burden directly affects:
Boss dialogue
Phase transitions
Rewards after victory

🧠 THEMATIC CORE
Greed is not wanting more.
Greed is refusing to release what already owns you.

✅ QUEST COMPLETION
You descend carrying exactly what you chose to keep.
